I could tell you what its like to be alone. To be stuck inside my head and never able to see outside my box. To hurt inside but yet unable to talk about it. I swear sometimes, I am the only one on earth who hurts as much as me. 

e.n.d.o.f.m.y.r.o.p.e.

Its almost July 31st... the day that Rob and I broke up last year. Gee, if you wouldve asked me 7 months ago, if Rob and I would be together today, I wouldve said no. Now if you ask me, I dont think I could live the rest of my life without him. When asked to define love in the mind, body, and soul... it is Rob. He is all that I could ever need. He is all that I ever want. To be this happy for this long, amazes me. To never get bored, and never long for something new... its wonderful. The constant in my life, is him.

LincolnJake: He is a good guy

I havent written in awhile, so I thought I'd update.

I wrecked my car and havent had it in a month or so. I'm staying at Rob's now and have been for a week or so now. I did have my mom's car and she had a rental but that became too much. 

I went to get my braces on June 29th and the date got pushed back until July 14th. They will def be put on then. I'm nervous. Today, a girl told me that I was vain for getting them so "late in life". I thought about it. It upset me for about a minute... I'm over it now. I'm still getting them so I guess her thoughts on the matter didnt matter too much. I want pretty teeth in my wedding pictures... not that I'm getting married anytime soon. 

Rob and I are better than ever. I love him so much. 

thats all for now.

In almost every situation that I have ever been in, I could understand who caused it and why its their fault. This time I can't, so I will type it out and see if it helps with the breaking down process.

Rob and I dated for ten months. I broke up with him because he was being completely unfair to me and he let me break it off because he was over it. Come the next morning, I wasnt so ok with it anymore but still, thats what he wanted it. We remained broken up for almost seven months. July 31st to February 20th. In that time he dated a girl named Lauren that he had worked with and been friends with previous to him and I dating. Still none the less, the idea of her made me uncomfortable and after one or two arguements about it, he decided that their emails would remain a secret. Anyways, they dated, happily I'm assuming for what he says was only 3 months. (Not true)  Rob cheated on Lauren with me the first time on Nov 22,2004 and this was to become a trend for him. We didnt talk again until January 1st 2005, Rob text messaged me. I let him know that my grandmother had died hours before and he called me after work. Over the next 3 weeks him and I went through a horrible display of mind games and heart break... he was playing the games while I was going through the heartbreak. He told me many times how unhappy he was with Lauren and that he wanted to leave her but couldnt. Couldnt that is until I went on a date with a guy that i really liked. He dumped her that very night and him and I went to lunch the next day to talk about what had to take place to make things right again. Keep in mind, the last seven months have been nothing but drunkin' phone calls and cheap one night stands from a guy that I love more than anything else. So, we work things out to the best of our ability and try to move on. It took more than anyone knows for me to let go and move on and I'm still struggling. Months pass and Rob is slowly changing. The other night he yelled at me for the first time and said somethings that he swears that he didnt mean. I dont know about you, but I was told all my life to think before I spoke because you cant take things back... I believe this to be common knowledge so I am confused that he doesnt understand that. The things that he said hurt me so bad that even my bones hurt. Then last night, while falling asleep, I said to him, "I'll be 20 in two months." He then replied, "Yup, almost July." My birthday is in August. So today, I was at his apartment getting ready for work. He left for class an hour before i had to be to work. I'm standing in his room, no where near the bed, and I say to myself, "God, help me out." and the phone falls off the bed. OUt of no where. So I pick it up, and I go through it. To say the least, rob deserves to be dumped... so I dumped him. I didnt cry on the phone and he swears that he didnt touch her. Regardless, he left too much room for doubt in a relationship that lacks it already. So I broke it off at 7:30pm. He was upset and said that he loved me. But when I got home, at 9:30 and got online, there he was. He didnt IM, or call me tonight at all. He admited to knowing that he was wrong. If I were wrong, I wouldve called all day until I got to explain myself and try to fix things. Wtf? 

anyone have a clue. help

I didnt read this over, so understand that I wrote it in the heat of the moment.

I'm sitting in rob's apartment with the worst cramps of my life... well not the worst but bad enough that I don't want to work out or go clock in to work. Damn it! 

Last night, my mom, my brother, rob and I all went to the Melting Pot for MOther's Day. The bill was $200!!! I couldnt believe it. I had so much fun though. We had so much food. I dont even like fondue that much but I still enjoyed it. I just dont like paying $80 on a plate and having to cook it myself. 

The other night, rob had  "boys night out" and called me before he went to bed. We had the best conversation in the world. I love him so much. 

The other night, Jin stayed the night and the guy came to my windows. She was freaked out but no one else in the world wouldve stayed the night. When the cops implied that we were crazy, she stood by her story. Shes my best friend and I could go on and on. I love that girl. 

this entry looks like a 5th grader wrote it haha.
Friends only...
